						<div class="fusion-text"><h3 class="title">The Art of Living</h3>
</div><div class="fusion-text"><p><img class="alignleft wp-image-48 size-medium" src="https://www.bertolinico.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/BertoliniCo-2011-05-24-at-1.08.18-PM-350x218.png" alt="Interior decorating - Bertolini Co - Borgo Lucignanello, Tuscany, Italy" width="350" height="218" srcset="https://www.bertolinico.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/BertoliniCo-2011-05-24-at-1.08.18-PM-350x218.png 350w, https://www.bertolinico.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/BertoliniCo-2011-05-24-at-1.08.18-PM-600x374.png 600w, https://www.bertolinico.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/BertoliniCo-2011-05-24-at-1.08.18-PM.png 793w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px" /></p>
</div><div class="fusion-text"><p>In the tiny medieval hamlet of Lucignano d”Asso, Borgo Lucignanello’s, historic houses have been transformed by Michael Bertolini with the Countess Piccolomini into stunning residences. The perfect place to enjoy an exclusive vacation in the Tuscan countryside. Any of these houses can be rented on a weekly, or monthly basis. More information can be found on the website, <a title="Borgo Lucignanello Historic Homes for Rent, Tuscany" href="https://www.borgolucignanello.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.borgolucignanello.com</a></p>
